article.headline: Binghamton 49, Stony Brook 44
article.story: EDS: Binghamton 49, Stony Brook 44. STONY BROOK, N.Y. (AP) -- Richard Forbes scored 16 points and Mike Gordon added 15 to lead Binghamton to a 49-44 victory over Stony Brook on Saturday. Ricky Lucas and Mitchell Beaufort both had 10 points for the Seawolves (6-22, 3-13 America East). Emanuel Neto's jumper with 11:59 to play closed out a game-opening 15-6 run for Stony Brook. The Bearcats (14-15, 9-7) went on a 16-2 run the rest of the half and Forbes closed it with a 3-pointer with less than a second left. A jumper by Demetri Young gave the Seawolves their last lead of the game, 31-30 with 12:29 to play. Gordon's jumper 2 minutes later gave Binghamton the lead for good.
